  "The solvent becomes heavier when solute is added": "",
  "Solute particles occupy surface area, reducing evaporation": "",
  "The temperature of the solution drops significantly": "",
  "The solute actually increases the evaporation rate": "",
  "Solute particles at the surface take up space that solvent molecules would otherwise occupy, reducing the number of solvent molecules that can escape into the gas phase.": "",
