  "The four colligative properties are: vapor pressure lowering, boiling point elevation, freezing point depression, and osmotic pressure.": "",
  "Which solution would have the lowest freezing point?": "",
  "Pure water with no dissolved solute at all": "",
  "0.5 M NaCl (producing 1.0 M total ion particles)": "",
  "1 M CaCl2 (producing 3 M total ion particles)": "",
  "1 M glucose (producing 1 M total molecules only)": "",
  "1 M CaCl2 produces the most particles (3 ions per formula unit: Ca2+ + 2 Cl-). More particles cause greater freezing point depression, so it has the lowest freezing point.": "",
